%F A238736 The condition for p to be a member of this sequence is A000129(p-e)/p == F(p-e, 2)/p == 0 (mod p), where F(p-e, 2) is the p-e'th Fibonacci polynomial evaluated at the argument 2, and e = (2/p) is a Jacobi Symbol.
%F A238736 Let PellQuotient(p) = A000129(p-e)/p, q_2 = (2^(p-1) - 1)/p = A007663(p) be the corresponding Fermat quotient of base 2, H(floor(p/8)) be a harmonic number, and e = (2/p) be a Jacobi Symbol. Then a result of Williams (1991), as refined by Sun (1995), shows that 2*PellQuotient(p) == -4*q_2 - H(floor(p/8)) (mod p).
%e A238736 PellQuotient(13) = 6214 = 13*478; PellQuotient(31) = 3470274850 = 31*111944350.
%t A238736 Select[Prime[Range[1000]], Mod[Fibonacci[# - JacobiSymbol[2, #], 2]/#, #] == 0 &]
